Similar to the first tearing delta zone, the qth tearing delta zone was generated when lqɛw=x<li. At this moment, the distance between the two jaws is smaller than the original length of the ith yarn. In other words, the number of weft yarns in the qth tearing delta zone is i-q. At this moment, the qth weft yarn had already been fractured, with the other i-q-1 weft yarns are in a tension state. The strain of each weft yarn in the qth delta zone could be expressed based on linear interpolation and the original length of the weft yarns. Accordingly, the tearing force applied on the weft yarns could be obtained as
